snippet.title: üîµSisters "Euthanized" Their Elderly Father | Linda Roberts | Police Interrogation
snippet.description:
Linda Roberts and Mary-Beth Tomaselli were charged with the first-degree murder of their 85-year-old father, who authorities thought died of natural causes in 2015. The sisters ‚Äì who escaped justice for four years ‚Äì were caught after Roberts confessed in 2019 to a man she‚Äôd had a sexual relationship with. Tomaselli slept with the same man!

The man, who has remained anonymous, recorded a conversation he had with Linda Roberts in which she confessed to killing her father with her sister. He recorded the confession on his phone and brought it to the local sheriff‚Äôs office. The two sisters, Linda Roberts, 61, and Mary-Beth Tomaselli, 63, pled guilty to the second-degree murder of their father, Anthony Tomaselli, in 2015.

The unnamed man recently had an interview with People, comparing the incident with his ex-lovers to the play Arsenic and Old Lace. He referenced the comedic play as he reflected on the sisters‚Äô plot, in which they killed their father and framed it on natural causes. ‚ÄúWho would suspect two old ladies killed their father?‚Äù he joked to the outlet.

The unnamed man and Robert‚Äôs confession, were able to piece together the full story. According to Detective Michael Bailey, Anthony Tomaselli, 85, was killed because he wouldn‚Äôt move into an assisted living facility in his old age.

Both Linda Roberts and Mary-Beth Tomaselli noticed that their father‚Äôs health and mental wellbeing were going downhill. After Anthony Tomaselli‚Äôs live-in girlfriend passed, his state took a turn for the worse, but he still wouldn‚Äôt budge.

That‚Äôs when Roberts and Tomaselli took a page out of Joseph Kesselring‚Äôs 1939 play, Arsenic and Old Lace, which tells the story of elderly sisters who murder old men in their home. According to reports, the sisters spiked their father‚Äôs nightly cocktail with a lethal dose of sleeping pills. The attempted poison didn‚Äôt do the trick, though, it only made their father sleepy.

To finish the job, the women placed a pillow over his head in an attempt to asphyxiate him. Then, Linda Roberts insisted that they ‚Äúget a washcloth and put it in his mouth,‚Äù according to Mary-Beth Tomaselli. ‚ÄúWe had to finish what we had started.‚Äù

The next morning, the women played it off as though their father died of natural causes. They called 911 and reported that their father wasn‚Äôt waking up, but that they had attempted CPR to no avail. Police did not suspect the elderly women, especially since Anthony Tomaselli had a long history of medical issues. The body was quickly cremated and the case was closed. Or so they thought.

‚ÄúThere were no red flags,‚Äù according to Detective Michael Bailey. ‚ÄúNobody suspected anything.‚Äù

Then, a new lover, who had been in bed with both sisters, learned the truth. Linda Roberts came clean to him during a nightly rant. ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt take it anymore ‚Äî I killed my father,‚Äù she told him. ‚ÄúWell, we did. We did it together.‚Äù

The man recorded the confession on his phone and in 2019 both Roberts and her sister were arrested and charged with first-degree murder. Without the confession, however, the sisters likely would have gotten away with murder.

snippet.title: Amber Heard says Johnny Depp trying to weasel out of trial date
snippet.description:
Read full article here: https://readnews.io/3q27l9



Amber Heard says exJohnny Depp is trying to play their Virginia judge like a fiddle by claiming he cant possibly make their January trial date  because hell be filming Fantastic Beasts III, new court papers show. The actor has made no effort whatsoever to work his schedule around the courts, assuming the role of pampered Hollywood star to a T, Heard seethed in documents filed Saturday,according to Britains The Sun. Mr Depp decided that, rather than speak with his employer to work his film commitments around his trial, he asks this court to subserviently reschedule around his employment and the entire film schedule and production, the actresss lawyers claimed. The Virginia documents were filed in response to Depps recent request to have his $50 million US defamation case against Heard pushed back till later next year. Depp is suing Heard over an op-edshe wrote in the Washington Post about being a victim of domestic abuse.  She didnt name Depp as her abuser, but she has repeatedly publicly alleged he horrifically attacked her before and during their marriage. Depp famously brought a similar case involving the Aquaman actress in Britain over a Sun headline calling him a wife beater.  The judge could rule in that case as early as this month. The Pirates of the Caribbean actor had argued in court papers in the Virginia case that the coronavirus pushed back the shooting on the latest installment of JK Rowlings Fanstastic Beasts movie franchise, creating an irreconcilable conflict for him with the trial. But Heards camp fired back in the new court papers, Although Mr Depp had been contacted in late June or July with the proposed filming dates, he did not alert movie bigs to the trial dates, The Sun said. The actress added that she is set to start filming Aquaman 2 in February  and that if the judge agreed with Depps request for a delay,

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Is OFFICIALLY The Worst Split In Hollywood After THIS..
snippet.description:
Let‚Äôs face it. Divorces are not only hard for the people involved, but are also messy, time consuming, and are pretty darn expensive. Especially if the divorcees are both huge people, there will be tons of dollars involved. But of all the messy divorces in the history of the entertainment industry, there will surely always be a couple that would dominate the list. From the scandalous split of Real Housewives of Beverly Hills cast Erika Jayne and her lawyer husband Tom Gerardi, to the heartbreaking separations of all time couple favorite Brad Pitt and Angelina Jolie, down to big industry names like Yolanda Hadid and David Foster, celebrity divorces are usually messy. And more often than not, they take up headlines for weeks. However, if there are two big names dominating the world of the ugliest divorces in Hollywood today, there might be no one else that may top off Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs divorce, which consequences are still being faced in an ongoing lawsuit up to this day. So of all these chaotic celebrity divorces, where do you think Amber Heard and Johnny Depp‚Äôs situation fall down? Is their situation really topsy turvy enough to top the worst couples who got divorced? Let‚Äôs find the answer to that in this video. But before anything else, make sure first to hit that subscribe button and smash that notification bell for more updates on Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs lawsuit case, and some other divorces that are dominating the internet today. Now, let‚Äôs dig in!

First, to be able to determine if Johnny and Amber‚Äôs messy marriage and divorce really does qualify to top this roster of the ugliest Hollywood divorces, let‚Äôs go back to the very beginning. Johnny Depp has been in the height of his career in the industry for many, many years now. This helped Johnny begin his acting career, landing more minor roles and then major ones. He also played a few roles with Helena Bonham Carter in many Tim Burton films such as Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, Alice in Wonderland and Alice Through the Looking Glass, Corpse Bride, Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street, and Dark Shadows. One of the most widely-known appearances of Johnny Depp that perhaps brought him the largest commercial and critical success was the Disney media franchise ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù series, where he landed and reprised his lead role for all five movies that ran from 2003 to 2017.

Amber Heard, on the other hand, started her acting career in 2003, first by appearing in two music videos, and then later on landing small supporting roles in three various television series. This then later on elevated her to more film and television roles, both supporting and lead actress. Her latest film that hit commercial success was the 2018 DC movie ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù, where she co-starred alongside Jason Momoa as Mera, the Atlantean Queen. Johnny and Amber first ignited a spark between them when they starred together in the 2011 comedy-drama film, The Rum Diary. The on-screen love story between the two has quickly travelled to real life.

In 2021, the 50 million dollar lawsuit has progressed in court, and there has been evidence that are springing out here and there that are helpful to the case of the former couple, including the recorded phone call where Despite all the evidence, since the lawsuit has not yet reached its final stage, Johnny is still currently enduring the blow of this predicament to his career, as it was also announced by Disney that Depp was relieved of his role as Jack Sparrow, one of his most famous roles in history.

As Amber Heard‚Äôs new movie, Aquaman 2, is about to be released by next year under the same production company that fired Johnny, the whole world of the internet is outraged. Because of this, the former couple‚Äôs divorce that happened in 2016 and has been finalized in 2017 still remains to be a hot topic during these days. Every now and then, new information and updates are surfacing about the couple, new evidences circulate as well, so it‚Äôs a little impossible for them not to hit the headlines all the time. In fact, Amber Heard even dropped some huge news just a couple of months ago.

That‚Äôs all for today, we hope you enjoyed that video, and if you agree that Johnny and Amber‚Äôs divorce counts as the worst, hit that like and subscribe button and smash that notification bell for more videos like this.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp's lawyers play video showing Amber Heard 'attacked' sister
snippet.description: LONDON (AP) ‚Äî Amber Heard's sister denied Friday that she had lied to a London court after Johnny Depp's lawyers in his libel suit against a British tabloid presented video footage that they claim showed his ex-wife was violent towards her.His legal team said they received the video from a "confidential" source on Thursday night, hours after Whitney Henriquez testified in court that she had never been attacked by Heard and that she was not frightened of her.Depp, 57, is suing News Group Newspapers, the publisher of The Sun, and the newspaper's executive editor, Dan Wootton, over an April 2018 article that labeled the actor a "wife beater." Depp has told the court that he was the one abused by Heard and that she had a history of being violent toward him.Johnny Depp vs. Amber Heard: All the nasty bits of the UK trial ‚Äî and it's all nastyThe Sun's defense relies on 14 allegations made by Heard of violence by Depp between 2013 and 2016, in settings as varied as a rented house in Australia, his private island in the Bahamas and a private jet.¬†The video at the heart of the court proceedings Friday, the final session before the two sides sum up their arguments, was unused reality TV footage from 2006 or 2007, according to Depp's lawyers, and shows Henriquez by a pool with a group of female friends. One of them is heard saying, "Did you get in a fight or something?" and "I can't believe Amber beat your ass." Another appears to inspect Henriquez's cheek and arm, and Henriquez says she is not going to talk about it.After viewing the video in court, Henriquez said the argument with her sister had been a "verbal" one and that her friends were "trying to make a very, very boring story more interesting."¬†Henriquez also denied that she had any injuries when the video was recorded and said that her friends were "looking for injuries that were not there, trying to create a narrative to make something more interesting, to create something out of nothing," she said.¬†Depp's lawyer, David Sherborne, had said earlier that it is "quite clear" that Heard assaulted her sister and that injuries to Henriquez are being examined on the tape.¬†Henriquez is a crucial witness in the trial as she has alleged to have seen Depp strike her sister. In her testimony on Thursday, Henriquez said Depp hit Heard "multiple times" during an alleged incident at the couple's Los Angeles apartment in March 2015. She also said that her sister had punched Depp on that occasion but only to defend her because she believed Depp was going to push Henriquez down the stairs.¬†Depp's lawyers have said that Henriquez tailored her evidence to meet her sister's version of events, especially around the "stairs" incident.¬†"Our case is she has lied in order to support her sister on this very important issue as to what happened on the stairs," Sherborne said.The court also heard evidence Friday from Heard's friend iO Tillett Wright, who said in his witness statement that Depp joked, after a wedding ceremony in
